cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.COM 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with interference management techniques in cellular networks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of frequency bands and their impact on coverage and rate. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper proposes an analytical model for evaluating FFR deployments. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper discusses the impact of interference on cell-edge users, who may be more likely to experience poor multimedia performance. 
- cs.COM (Computers and Society) is a less likely category, but the paper does touch on the impact of FFR on access to different tiers of the network, which could have social implications.
